OL,3,CHusband left performing medical
OL,4,Cprocedure on wife who wasn't 'offered
OL,5,Coperation'
OL,7,FLinda and her husband Paul, who are
OL,8,Ffrom Walsall, said doctors have been
OL,9,Ftrying to treat the prolapse with
OL,10,Fpessaries, but due to her muscle
OL,11,Fweakness from her Parkinsons, that
OL,12,Fhasn't worked.
OL,14,FAnd, they say, instead of offering her
OL,15,Fa hysterectomy sooner, Paul has had to
OL,16,Fperform a medical procedure himself to
OL,17,Fcorrect the prolapse.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
