OL,7,FShe said if she had been offered
OL,8,Fsurgery sooner then she would have
OL,9,Fbeen fitter to face it.
OL,11,FThe couple are both hoping that the
OL,12,Fsurgery means Linda will be able to
OL,13,Flive the life she did before, with
OL,14,FPaul describing the debilitating
OL,15,Fnature of the prolapse as meaning he
OL,16,Fhas 'lost his best friend.'
